entries.femaleVariant: Good evening, Night City. We begin tonight with, uh...
Panic has saturated the market... This latest slump has led to losses in excess of 500 billion eurodollars.
In the wake of another attack on Arasaka's Night City HQ, the, uh, Japanese goliath has plummeted by 17 percent. And we should expect that slide to continue, say analysts.
According to a statement from the NCPD, a terrorist cell is believed to be responsible, but it remains unknown who funded the attack and why.
In light of these events, I have only one recommendation, my friends. Sell.
Sell now, while you still can.
Arasaka CEO, Yorinobu Arasaka, has since evacuated his Night City office for Tokyo.
We begin with a look at the stock market. As usual.
